Chama Cha Demokrasia na Maendeleo (Chadema)'s Executive Council has endorsed the Central Committee decision to suspend 19 members, who double as Special Seat Members of the Parliament. The decision which was reached by the party's highest decision-making body on Wednesday night was among five issues slated for opposition party's General Assembly meeting held in Dar es Salaam. Another agenda was the appointment of members of the party's board of trustees following the demise of of Mr Arcado Ntagazwa. The veteran politician died in February, last year. Of the sacked MPs, there is Halima Mdee who is the former Chadema's Women Wing Council chairperson Halima Mdee plus other Youth wing Council leaders. It is claimed that the suspended l members assumed the role of Special Seat MPs without the authorisation of the party. The MPs challenges against the the Central Committee's decision on stripping their membership until Wednesday when the council quashed their appeals.